Downloading Images

Since the COCO dataset is very lerge I will first download sample file using fastai and when thing start working I will scale it.

from fastai2.vision.all import *

# downloading images
img_path = untar_data(URLs.COCO_SAMPLE)
Path.BASE_PATH = img_path
img_path.ls()

(#2) [Path('annotations'),Path('train_sample')]

Annotation contating lots of file. For this project we don't need all of them. We have two annotation file: train and valid. Let's look into the train annotation json file

f = open('annotations/captions_train2014.json')
annot = json.load(f)

*Since json file works similar to python dictionary. It's easy to explore using dictionary finction.**
